            "body": "<p>I think the error is related to this error message:<\/p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>This can also happen if you are @ComponentScanning a springframework package (e.g. if you put a @ComponentScan in the default package by mistake).<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<p>If I correctly see from your screenshot the <code>Helloer.java<\/code> is in the default package of your project. You need to move it into <code>ca.company<\/code> package. Also as you already define the <code>B<\/code> class as component you don't need to configure another <code>B<\/code> bean in the <code>Config<\/code> class.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 61989219,
            "question_id": 61988863
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/d99204bcce923f40f5c72b7f80121644?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 2139538,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1898563,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1898563/michael",
                "reputation": 44485,
                "display_name": "Michael",
                "accept_rate": 78
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1590339605,
            "creation_date": 1590339605,
            "body": "<p>If you don't require the database autoconfiguration, you can explicitly opt-out of it.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>@EnableAutoConfiguration(exclude = {DataSourceAutoConfiguration.class, DataSourceTransactionManagerAutoConfiguration.class, HibernateJpaAutoConfiguration.class})\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>See also <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/36387265/disable-all-database-related-auto-configuration-in-spring-boot\">Disable all Database related auto configuration in Spring Boot<\/a> <\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 61989393,
            "question_id": 61988863
        }
